The paper deals with mechanism design theory, which is a subfield of game theory and economics. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and heuristics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with optimization problems, which could place it in cs.EC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
